  carbohydrates: 106 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 920 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-beef-bowls-64497813fe002647e40c54bf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Asian
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @red bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add @peanuts{1/2%ounce}, 2 TBSP water, and @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings). Cook, stirring often, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until tender and lightly browned, ~{6-9%minutes}.

Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Add a drizzle of oil to same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until beef is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in veggies, then add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until mixture is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

> Swap in turkey for beef if preferred.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and lime zest to taste. Season with @salt{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with beef mixture, peanuts, and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.